implistic conceptualizations of truth, an emancipation from the "must-be" that implies an ever-to-be-renewed renegotiation—a responsability that has much to do with the act of critique or interpretation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362692840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626928/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles